
[1]perceive

   PERCE'IVE, v.t. [L. percipio; per and capio, to take.]

   1. To have knowledge or receive impressions of external objects through
   the medium or instrumentality of the senses or bodily organs; as, to
   perceive light or color; to perceive the cold or ice or the taste of
   honey.

   2. To know; to understand; to observe.

   Till we ourselves see it with our own eyes, and perceive it by our own
   understanding, we are in the dark.

   3. To be affected by; to receive impressions from.

   The upper regions of the air perceive the collection of the matter of
   tempests before the air below.
